{
  "local_port": 40578,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I register my mobile number with UAN?",
  "response": "To register your mobile number with your Universal Account Number (UAN) in India, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the EPFO Website**: Go to the official Employee Provident Fund Organisation (EPFO) website: [epfindia.gov.in](https://www.epfindia.gov.in).\n\n2. **Access the UAN Member Portal**: Click on the \"UAN Portal\" or go directly to the UAN member portal. The direct link is usually [unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in](https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in).\n\n3. **Log in to Your Account**: Enter your UAN, password, and the captcha code to log in. If you haven't registered your UAN yet, you will need to do that first.\n\n4. **Click on 'Manage'**: Once logged in, find the 'Manage' section in the menu.\n\n5. **Select \u2018Update KYC\u2019**: In the drop-down under the 'Manage' option, select \u2018Update KYC\u2019.\n\n6. **Enter Your Mobile Number**: In the KYC details section, you can find the option to update your mobile number. Enter your mobile number in the provided field.\n\n7. **Submit the Request**: After entering your mobile number, submit the request.\n\n8. **Verify Your Mobile Number**: An OTP (One-Time Password) will be sent to the mobile number you entered. Enter this OTP to verify and confirm the mobile number registration.\n\n9. **Confirmation**: Once verified, your mobile number will be successfully linked to your UAN.\n\nIf you have any difficulties, you may also visit your regional EPFO office for assistance or consult the help desk provided on the EPFO website.",
